# Error Handling & Logging Guidelines

## 1. Exception Handling
- Always raise **meaningful exceptions**:
  ```python
  raise ValueError(f"Invalid user ID {user_id}. Expected integer, got {type(user_id)}")
Prefer custom exception classes for better debugging.

## 2. Logging Practices
Use structured logging (structlog or logging).
Log errors with context (e.g., request ID, user ID, timestamp).
Ensure logs are machine-readable for monitoring tools.

[logging_config.py](mdc:backend/src/config/logging_config.py) is the central logger for the project